<mdl:Grid xmlns:fx="http://ns.adobe.com/mxml/2009"
			  xmlns:js="library://ns.apache.org/royale/basic"
			  xmlns:mdl="library://ns.apache.org/royale/mdl">
	<mdl:style>
		<js:AllCSSStyles maxWidth="900" margin="auto"/>
	</mdl:style>		
	<mdl:GridCell column="12">
		<mdl:Card width="100%">
			<mdl:style>
				<js:AllCSSStyles minHeight="0" />
			</mdl:style>
			<mdl:CardTitle>
				<mdl:CardTitleText text="Hello Royale Developers!"/>
			</mdl:CardTitle>
			<mdl:CardSupportingText>
				<mdl:style>
					<js:SimpleCSSStyles fontSize="16"/>
				</mdl:style>
			 	<mdl:beads>
                    <js:InnerHTML>
                         <![CDATA[
							I would like to present my idea of helping you with your first steps in <a href="http://royale.apache.org/">Apache Royale&trade;</a> framework. Basically, I will provide brief information, tutorials and updates from the community area using <a href="https://www.patreon.com/piotrzarzycki">Patreon</a>, <a href="https://github.com/piotrzarzycki21/TranspiledActionScript">GitHub</a> and <a href="https://transpiledactionscript.com/">TranspiledActionScript.com</a> website.
							]]>
                    </js:InnerHTML>
                 </mdl:beads>		
            </mdl:CardSupportingText>
		</mdl:Card>
		<mdl:Card width="100%">
			<mdl:style>
				<js:AllCSSStyles minHeight="0" />
			</mdl:style>
			<mdl:CardTitle>
				<mdl:CardTitleText text="Patreon"/>
			</mdl:CardTitle>
			<mdl:CardSupportingText>
				<mdl:style>
					<js:SimpleCSSStyles fontSize="16"/>
				</mdl:style>
			 	<mdl:beads>
                    <js:InnerHTML>
                         <![CDATA[
							This place will be the central point of information. I will provide you updates from the Apache Royale&trade; community, some development nuances and some examples through the GitHub repository. However, my support will have a <b>time limit of one year</b>, counting from the start date. After that time, I will review what I was able to achieve and whether people are still seeking my help. Each donation through <a href="https://www.patreon.com/piotrzarzycki">Patreon</a> will allow me to extend the amount of time, which I can spend on this idea, and thus to be more flexible in terms of the content that can appear here.
							]]>
                    </js:InnerHTML>
                 </mdl:beads>		
            </mdl:CardSupportingText>
		</mdl:Card>
		<mdl:Card width="100%">
			<mdl:style>
				<js:AllCSSStyles minHeight="0" />
			</mdl:style>
			<mdl:CardTitle>
				<mdl:CardTitleText text="Website"/>
			</mdl:CardTitle>
			<mdl:CardSupportingText>
				<mdl:style>
					<js:SimpleCSSStyles fontSize="16"/>
				</mdl:style>
			 	<mdl:beads>
                    <js:InnerHTML>
                         <![CDATA[
							The <a href="https://transpiledactionscript.com/">TranspiledActionScript.com</a> website will serve as a gateway to Patreon and the Github repository, as well as a place where you will be able to see all created examples live. The website will be developed using Apache Royale&trade; and its <a href="https://github.com/piotrzarzycki21/TranspiledActionScript/tree/examples/Examples/TranspiledActionScriptWebsite">sources</a> will become a part of the repository examples.
							]]>
                    </js:InnerHTML>
                 </mdl:beads>		
            </mdl:CardSupportingText>
		</mdl:Card>
		<mdl:Card width="100%">
			<mdl:style>
				<js:AllCSSStyles minHeight="0" />
			</mdl:style>
			<mdl:CardTitle>
				<mdl:CardTitleText text="GitHub Repository"/>
			</mdl:CardTitle>
			<mdl:CardSupportingText>
				<mdl:style>
					<js:SimpleCSSStyles fontSize="16"/>
				</mdl:style>
			 	<mdl:beads>
                    <js:InnerHTML>
                         <![CDATA[
							The <a href="https://github.com/piotrzarzycki21/TranspiledActionScript">TranspiledActionScript</a> repository will store not only the source code of the provided examples, but also all articles not restricted to patrons in the form of <a href="https://github.com/piotrzarzycki21/TranspiledActionScript/wiki/How-it-works%3F">Wiki</a> pages. The idea of how the repository is going to work as well as the release process is described in <a href="https://github.com/piotrzarzycki21/TranspiledActionScript/blob/master/README.md">README</a> file.
						  ]]>
                    </js:InnerHTML>
                 </mdl:beads>		
            </mdl:CardSupportingText>
		</mdl:Card>
		<mdl:Card width="100%">
			<mdl:CardTitle>
				<mdl:CardTitleText text="I have a question related to Apache Royale. Where should I ask it?"/>
			</mdl:CardTitle>	
			<mdl:CardSupportingText>
				<mdl:style>
					<js:SimpleCSSStyles fontSize="16"/>
				</mdl:style>
				<mdl:beads>
					<js:InnerHTML>
					<![CDATA[
					The best place to ask questions is Apache Royale&trade; <a href="http://apache-royale-development.20373.n8.nabble.com/">development</a> or <a href="http://apache-royale-users.20374.n8.nabble.com/">users</a> mailing lists. However, I will also be happy to answer to any issues raised in the <a href="https://github.com/piotrzarzycki21/TranspiledActionScript/issues">GitHub repository</a> or in the comments section under Patreon articles.</br></br>
					I hope you will enjoy this place and find the answers you seek,</br>
					Piotr
					]]>
					</js:InnerHTML>
				</mdl:beads>
			</mdl:CardSupportingText>
		</mdl:Card>
	</mdl:GridCell>		
</mdl:Grid>